1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:04,140
I know you've worked here part-time,
so you know most of this.

2
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:07,110
But things look a little different
when you're the owner.

3
00:00:07,710 --> 00:00:11,450
The key to our business is catering
to each customer's individual tastes.

4
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,020
Of course.
That's why we use individual pots...

5
00:00:14,020 --> 00:00:16,020
so that each person can
customize their meal...

6
00:00:16,020 --> 00:00:17,520
and everything stays hygienic.

7
00:00:18,090 --> 00:00:20,930
Our customers really appreciate
that about us.

8
00:00:20,930 --> 00:00:21,960
You're right.

9
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:25,730
We have a variety of broths and sauces
so that they can pick and choose.

10
00:00:25,930 --> 00:00:28,730
So they can have fun creating
their own combinations.

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,040
You know you must be meticulous
with ingredients,

12
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:34,570
like vegetables and seafood, right?

13
00:00:34,740 --> 00:00:36,410
Yes, I'll keep that in mind.

14
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:39,740
You know how young people love
mala hot pot these days, right?

15
00:00:39,940 --> 00:00:41,350
Since we have a mala broth,

16
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:44,920
customers love that the whole family
can enjoy a meal together here.

17
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:48,520
Exactly. You really know your stuff
since you've worked here.

18
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:49,890
Of course I do.

19
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,660
You're not Seo Rin, are you?

20
00:00:53,730 --> 00:00:56,290
What? Ma'am, what are you talking about?

21
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:59,630
I've been watching you,
and a lot of things don't add up.

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,530
Since when have you ever made your bed?

23
00:01:02,530 --> 00:01:04,070
Now it's always neatly folded.

24
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:06,570
You used to hate sweet rice punch,
but now you're always asking for it.

25
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:08,870
And you won't even eat the fish eyeballs
you used to love so much.

26
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,740
And on top of all that,
you're cleaning the floor?

27
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:14,480
You're not the type to do these things.
I know you.

28
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:17,320
Stop it! Just be quiet, please!

29
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,180
I'm right, aren't I? You're not Seo Rin.

30
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:21,450
Stop! Ma'am...

31
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,520
Seo Rin.

32
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:28,830
Why are you covering her mouth like that?

33
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:31,330
- What on earth is going on?
- What?

34
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:34,600
Ma'am, tell me.

35
00:01:35,170 --> 00:01:38,140
Why was Seo Rin covering your mouth
like that?

36
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,490
I said to tell me what this was all about.

37
00:01:55,790 --> 00:01:59,090
Mom, it's nothing.
She was just spouting nonsense.

38
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,630
Ma'am, I have something to tell you.

39
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:02,890
Mrs. Yang!

40
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:07,970
This is all messed up. It's all over now.

41
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:10,940
I'm just so upset.

42
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,910
I was bringing her some juice,
and I spilled it.

43
00:02:14,570 --> 00:02:18,210
Then she yelled at me
that I can't do one thing right,

44
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:20,480
so I lost my temper and talked back.

45
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:23,210
That's when she covered my mouth
and started making this huge scene.

46
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:25,380
Mrs. Yang.

47
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:28,920
When you've made a mistake,
just admit to it.

48
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,220
Do you really have to make excuses?

49
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:32,560
You had it coming.

50
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:34,930
And here I thought
it was something serious.

51
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:38,530
Mrs. Yang, how dare you get angry
at Seo Rin?

52
00:02:38,530 --> 00:02:39,630
The nerve of you.

53
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:43,400
Really?
Fine. I guess it was all my fault then.

54
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:49,410
What is with her attitude?

55
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:54,080
Just because Father kept her on
because he likes her cooking,

56
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:56,550
she's starting to think she's a big shot.

57
00:02:57,980 --> 00:03:00,450
Tell me about it.
It's complete insubordination.

58
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:03,990
Why did she cover for me?

59
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:11,960
What on earth have I done?

60
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,600
If that girl isn't Seo Rin,
then who is she?

61
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:39,420
- Mrs. Yang.
- I'm so curious that I can't let this go.

62
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,960
Tell me the truth.

63
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,830
What's your real name?

64
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:46,860
It's Oh Jang Mi.

65
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:48,130
Oh Jang Mi?

66
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,100
Why is your last name Oh?

67
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,140
You look exactly like Ma Seo Rin.

68
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,870
Are you...

69
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:55,870
twins?

70
00:03:56,510 --> 00:03:58,310
Yes, that's right.

71
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,580
Seo Rin and I are twins.

72
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,220
Goodness, what on earth happened?

73
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:25,000
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

74
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,240
That is...

75
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:33,310
- where I used to live.
- Tae Pyung's making a fortune.

76
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,310
Look at all these lunch boxes.

77
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,280
You're making a lot of money.

78
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:39,850
Uncle, are you going to sell all this?

79
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:41,090
I am.

80
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,620
That's my mom.

81
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:48,930
So you and Seo Rin are twins,

82
00:04:49,290 --> 00:04:52,200
and CEO Chae Hwa Young kidnapped Seo Rin
and raised her as her own?

83
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,470
Yes.

84
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:57,240
She's the reason my mom is in that state,

85
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,210
had my father killed
so I wouldn't be discovered,

86
00:05:01,910 --> 00:05:05,040
and even tried to kill me
and Seo Rin in a truck accident.

87
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:08,610
Is that true?

88
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,080
I know it's hard to believe,

89
00:05:10,550 --> 00:05:11,550
but it's all true.

90
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:14,590
I just haven't found
any hard evidence yet,

91
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:15,990
which is why I'm doing all this.

92
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:19,990
I knew Chae Hwa Young was a nasty person,

93
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:21,760
but how could anyone be so evil?

94
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,000
That makes me so mad.

95
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:28,130
I'm going to make Chae Hwa Young pay
for what she's done.

96
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:33,640
I couldn't just go and tell Grandfather
with only circumstantial evidence,

97
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:38,540
but I can't just let her get away
with this.

98
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:42,480
You're right. I don't blame you.

99
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:47,420
But it's uncanny
how much you look like Seo Rin.

100
00:05:48,290 --> 00:05:49,990
Your personalities seem
a little different, though.

101
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:51,960
Thank you.

102
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:54,890
I nearly had a heart attack earlier.

103
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:58,860
Without your help, my revenge, everything,
would've gone up in smoke.

104
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,370
How could I not help you?

105
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,670
Thanks to you, she's stopped hitting me,
and my life has gotten a little better.

106
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:08,270
Still, I'm grateful.

107
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:11,380
But you need to be careful.

108
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:13,910
Even when you're getting your revenge,
you have to be careful.

109
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:15,910
I know.

110
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:18,120
The people in this family...

111
00:06:18,650 --> 00:06:19,880
are something else.

112
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:28,160
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

113
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,180
Professor Kang?

114
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:49,810
This is...

115
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:52,320
Ma Dae Chang from Dream Group.

116
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:53,990
Pardon?

117
00:06:55,450 --> 00:06:56,750
Hello, Chairman.

118
00:06:57,020 --> 00:07:00,320
To what do I owe the call?

119
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,590
I'll get right to the point.

120
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:05,860
Are you free tomorrow evening?

121
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:07,800
I was thinking of inviting you to my home.

122
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,170
Me?

123
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:14,810
May I ask what the occasion is?

124
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:17,440
No special reason.

125
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,480
I heard you were on the Dream Project
with my daughter-in-law,

126
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,510
so I wanted to have a little chat.

127
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:27,290
And I heard you sent a bouquet
to congratulate her on her award.

128
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:29,820
I appreciate the thoughtful gesture.

129
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:33,660
A gesture like that is hard to ignore.

130
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:38,360
Chairman, I didn't actually send
the flowers myself...

131
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:41,930
In any case, you laid the groundwork
for our Dream Project.

132
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,430
And I'm grateful to you
for that, Professor Kang.

133
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:48,410
I'd like to treat you to dinner as thanks,
so please don't refuse my invitation.

134
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:51,480
Then I'll assume you're coming.
I'll be waiting.

135
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:52,910
Chairman.

136
00:07:53,610 --> 00:07:56,380
Yes. I'll see you tomorrow.

137
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:06,160
Why on earth would Chairman Ma
invite me to his home?

138
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:10,560
I never knew love
could be this complicated.

139
00:08:15,130 --> 00:08:18,500
Come on, Hwa Young.
Please pick up the phone, Hwa Young!

140
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:24,110
(Professor Kang)

141
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,150
First, Yeom San Wol tails me,
snapping pictures.

142
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:38,060
Then Jin Hong Ju puts on a show,
pretending Professor Kang sent them.

143
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:40,690
Do you two know something
to be doing this?

144
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:42,960
Are you trying to pressure me?

145
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:44,830
The nerve.

146
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,140
I already played along
and said Professor Kang sent them,

147
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:54,140
so I can't call out Jin Hong Ju on it now.

148
00:08:57,210 --> 00:09:00,380
Regarding the facility infrastructure,
will you...

149
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,190
Ma'am? Is something wrong?

150
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,520
What's wrong? This isn't like you, Mom.

151
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,290
Are you even listening to us?

152
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,290
Yes, of course I'm listening.

153
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:16,960
And Director Ma.

154
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,660
Are you going to keep calling me "Mom"
at the office?

155
00:09:20,330 --> 00:09:21,330
Team Leader Jin.

156
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:25,500
I trust you are addressing Director Ma
with the proper respect.

157
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:27,970
Keep your personal and professional lives
completely separate.

158
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,980
Don't bring your family drama
into the office.

159
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,510
Yes, ma'am.

160
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:43,350
Okay, I've made up my mind.

161
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:45,460
I'm going to tell the truth.

162
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:49,590
What?

163
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:52,000
- You're home early.
- Yes.

164
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:53,060
Aren't you working on your paper?

165
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,170
It seems like all you do
is just fool around these days.

166
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:59,400
What are you going to do if you get fired?

167
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:02,070
Are you rubbing it in my face
that you make more money than me?

168
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:03,770
Oh my gosh, listen to you.

169
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:05,880
I was just joking.

170
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,150
All right.

171
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:09,510
Listen, about Jun Ho.

172
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:13,220
There's no way he's marrying
the Dream Group's granddaughter.

173
00:10:13,820 --> 00:10:15,050
I've made myself clear.

174
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,360
You're being so weird.

175
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:19,360
Why on earth not?

176
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:21,560
This would be a huge step up for Jun Ho.

177
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:25,530
For a marriage to work,
a couple needs to be on a similar footing.

178
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:29,000
Do you think marrying rich
guarantees happiness?

179
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:32,340
Gosh. It doesn't matter what we say.

180
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,870
It all comes down to how Jun Ho feels.

181
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:37,910
He's the one getting married,
so I'm going to respect his decision.

182
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:40,110
Goodness.

183
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:48,050
Are you still uncomfortable around me?

184
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:50,450
Because there are too many things
that don't add up.

185
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:54,990
Don't overthink it.
Just take it at face value.

186
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,830
Is it that hard to be on my side?

187
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,360
That's what I'm wondering.

188
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,970
Out of all the employees here,

189
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,100
why me, of all people?

190
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:08,410
No matter how much I think about it,
I just don't get it.

191
00:11:08,770 --> 00:11:10,810
It's because my daughter,
Seo Rin, likes you.

192
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:16,110
You're the only one
Seo Rin has gone after like this.

193
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,450
As a parent, I want to see my daughter
end up with the man she likes.

194
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:23,390
And when that man happens to be
a brilliant talent,

195
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:25,360
what more could I ask for, right?

196
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,260
But...

197
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:30,800
I never said I wanted
to marry Director Ma.

198
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:33,500
Don't my feelings matter?

199
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,370
Spreading rumors like this puts me
in a tough spot.

200
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:41,810
I know you're not seeing anyone.

201
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:45,540
Being single doesn't mean I have to marry
someone I don't love, like Director Ma.

202
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,310
Then just start loving her now.

203
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,950
I've told you this countless times.

204
00:11:51,550 --> 00:11:54,690
My Seo Rin is a good catch.

205
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:03,890
Thank you, son.

206
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,000
Goodness, you're so thoughtful.

207
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,300
Jun Ho.

208
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:15,940
When will I ever get to hold you?

209
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:20,780
When can I finally tell you that
I'm your mother without feeling ashamed?

210
00:12:21,780 --> 00:12:22,880
My son, Jun Ho...

211
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,530
Hey, it's the black spiral notebook,
right?

212
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:39,960
Yes, it has my notes for the meeting.
I can't believe I forgot it.

213
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:43,200
What? So even Mr. Perfect can slip up.
This is a first.

214
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,700
Stop messing around and just bring it.

215
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:46,900
To the hotel?

216
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:49,110
Hey, I'm a busy man.

217
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:50,540
Do you know what my hourly rate is?

218
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,140
How could you ask me to run an errand?

219
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:53,240
Don't get smart with me.

220
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:55,180
Hurry up and bring it.
I'm running out of time.

221
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:58,350
All right, I'll bring it to the hotel now.

222
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:01,490
Your brother asked you
to bring that to the hotel?

223
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:02,590
Yes.

224
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,660
He must have his head in the clouds,
making mistakes he never used to.

225
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:08,360
Anyway, I'll drop this off
and then head to work.

226
00:13:08,490 --> 00:13:09,830
Okay, go on. See you later.

227
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,640
Hong Ju? It's me.

228
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:26,180
- Is now a good time to talk?
- Yes, Ms. Han.

229
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,550
This is an early call. Is everything okay?

230
00:13:29,210 --> 00:13:32,720
Baek Ho is on his way
to the hotel for an errand,

231
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,890
and I thought if you two
bumped into each other,

232
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,320
as if by chance or fate, it'd be perfect.

233
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:40,360
What? Baek Ho is coming to the hotel?

234
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,830
Thank you, Ms. Han.
I'll come see you soon.

235
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,900
What are you so happy about?

236
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:55,340
If things go well,
I might even marry Lawyer Kang this year.

237
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,440
What? Get married?

238
00:13:58,180 --> 00:13:59,440
How's my outfit?

239
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,980
It's awful, isn't it?
It's not really feminine, is it?

240
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:04,180
It isn't. It's unflattering.

241
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:05,980
I knew it.

242
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,620
This won't do.

243
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:09,790
I need to go change.

244
00:14:14,730 --> 00:14:16,930
Marrying Baek Ho?

245
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:25,400
Hey, Jun Ho. I'm here. Where are you?

246
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:28,410
Just leave it at the front desk.
I don't have time to come down right now.

247
00:14:28,970 --> 00:14:30,770
You make me run an errand,
and you can't even bother to come down?

248
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,440
Whatever.

249
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:35,250
Just you wait. I'll get you back for this.

250
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,750
Excuse me.

251
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:42,090
Baek Ho.

252
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:45,960
Seeing you at least like this
is a breath of fresh air.

253
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,530
There's no way I'm marrying
General Manager Kang.

254
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:51,130
Thank you.

255
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,400
Baek Ho! What brings you here?

256
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,140
I had some business to take care of.

257
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:02,670
If I'd known you'd be here,
I would've dressed a little nicer.

258
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:04,940
I look like a total mess today.

259
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:07,140
You look fine to me.

260
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:10,150
Oh, so this is the style you like.

261
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:13,120
Since we ran into each other,
do you want to grab a coffee?

262
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,390
Sorry, I don't have the time.

263
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:20,990
You still owe me that drink, right?

264
00:15:21,390 --> 00:15:22,460
I'll call you.

265
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:24,230
They're getting drinks?

266
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:36,040
Baek Ho.

267
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:38,740
You haven't forgotten about me, have you?

268
00:15:41,010 --> 00:15:42,150
Baek Ho.

269
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:47,150
(Organizational Structure
and Divisional Responsibilities)

270
00:15:47,220 --> 00:15:51,190
(Project Strategy Overview)

271
00:15:52,790 --> 00:15:53,990
Alright, let's begin.

272
00:15:54,330 --> 00:15:56,960
With the launch of Phase Two
of the Dream Project,

273
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,860
I will now outline the responsibilities
for each department.

274
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:03,430
We need to be crystal clear
on who's responsible for what.

275
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:04,740
Go ahead.

276
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:05,870
Yes, sir.

277
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:11,310
First up, Team Leader Jin Hong Ju
will be heading up marketing.

278
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,040
New audience analysis, brand renewal,

279
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,810
brand expansion, and communications.

280
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:18,080
- Please elaborate.
- Yes.

281
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:20,380
To attract our younger demographic,

282
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:22,850
we plan on launching a new brand.

283
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,090
Let's not focus exclusively on
the Millennial and Gen Z generations.

284
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:28,230
Understood, ma'am.

285
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:31,360
Next up is
the Food and Beverages operations,

286
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,960
as well as the planning
for the Wellness Complex.

287
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:36,330
Both will be overseen
by Director Ma Seo Rin.

288
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,370
- Yes.
- You can refer...

289
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:41,770
to the Bali and Singapore trips
you took before.

290
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:45,040
- Director Ma.
- Yes? Yes, of course.

291
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:49,750
The Wellness Complex will be based on
traditional healing therapies.

292
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:51,550
Excellent, General Manager Kang.

293
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:54,690
Our buyers will love that, Chairman.

294
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:59,090
You need to know how to read
global trends.

295
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,930
I've already made the introductions
to the buyers.

296
00:17:01,990 --> 00:17:04,900
Stop trying to take credit
for every little thing.

297
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,660
Show me results.

298
00:17:07,830 --> 00:17:09,030
Yes, Chairman.

299
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:15,270
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

300
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:18,540
That old man.
He can't say anything nicely.

301
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:20,580
Mom.

302
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,280
Did you hear?

303
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:24,650
Grandpa wants everyone for dinner tonight.

304
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:27,350
He wants you home early, so don't miss it.

305
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:29,120
That dinner is going to give me an ulcer.

306
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,220
Why the sudden dinner invitation?

307
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:35,430
But Mom, you never know.
He might have something important to say.

308
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:40,000
That's true. For him to summon us
for a meal out of the blue...

309
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,330
I'm heading out. See you at home.

310
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:43,770
Alright.

311
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:45,800
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

312
00:17:48,410 --> 00:17:50,710
What could that old man want to say?

313
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:51,980
You don't think...

314
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:54,240
he wants to talk about the will, do you?

315
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,050
That could be it.

316
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,030
A party? All of a sudden?

317
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:14,630
It was Seo Rin's idea
to throw you a celebratory party.

318
00:18:16,070 --> 00:18:18,870
Oh, honey. This is so unlike you.

319
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,300
Surprise!

320
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,610
Of course.

321
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:24,840
After a bouquet from a man,
she certainly deserves a party.

322
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:26,640
- Absolutely.
- Yeom San Wol.

323
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:28,310
Will you shut your mouth?

324
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:31,150
By the way, I've invited a guest.

325
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:32,820
You invited a guest?

326
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:34,520
Who?

327
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:36,350
It can't be Jun Ho, can it?

328
00:18:39,290 --> 00:18:40,390
Here he comes now.

329
00:18:43,190 --> 00:18:45,160
Professor Kang, welcome.

330
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:46,900
Hello, Chairman.

331
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,030
Thank you for having me.

332
00:18:54,510 --> 00:18:55,510
CEO Chae.

333
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:59,810
Professor Kang? What are you doing here?

334
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:03,450
- Father.
- I invited him.

335
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:06,420
To congratulate you on your award.

336
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,990
He invited me to have dinner with you.

337
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:10,350
It's nice to see you, Professor.

338
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:12,160
Thank you for coming, Professor.

339
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:15,060
All right, let's have a seat.
Is dinner not ready yet?

340
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:16,530
No, it's all ready.

341
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:19,230
Mrs. Yang, dinner's ready, right?

342
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,480
Why are you here, anyway?

343
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:34,110
Is there something you wanted to tell me?

344
00:19:35,210 --> 00:19:37,110
No. It's nothing like that.

345
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,520
I can't just tell you
that your father's having an affair...

346
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:43,090
with CEO Chae Hwa Young of all people.

347
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,320
Tae Pyung, what's going on?

348
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:52,660
I'm busy with the lunch boxes,
so let's talk later, Baek Ho.

349
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,300
What is it? Tell me.

350
00:19:59,870 --> 00:20:02,740
That's strange.
He's definitely hiding something.

351
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:05,940
What is he hiding from me?

352
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:17,650
All they said was not to trust CEO Chae.
Why haven't they called again?

353
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:19,460
I'm dying of curiosity.

354
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:22,490
Did they mean...

355
00:20:23,290 --> 00:20:24,490
I shouldn't trust her...

356
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:28,130
because she's cheating
with Professor Kang?

357
00:20:44,820 --> 00:20:47,950
Professor Kang.
How are you enjoying the meal?

358
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:49,920
Yes, it's delicious.

359
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,590
Your housekeeper...

360
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:54,020
seems to be an excellent cook.

361
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:58,760
By the way, I heard you had a big ordeal
while working on the Dream Project.

362
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,200
Is everything all right now?

363
00:21:02,670 --> 00:21:04,370
- Yes.
- That's right.

364
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,070
Someone died in that car accident, right?

365
00:21:07,770 --> 00:21:10,870
Professor, what were you doing there
at that time anyway?

366
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,210
What do you mean by that?

367
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:15,710
Seo Rin, do you know something
about that incident?

368
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:19,580
Do you think I'm clueless
about what goes on at the company?

369
00:21:19,850 --> 00:21:22,490
Everyone knows.
Did you think I'd be the only one not to?

370
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:27,390
Come on, Professor.
Please tell us. I'm dying to know.

371
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:31,800
Right, just as Seo Rin said,
I was curious about that myself.

372
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:35,770
I was at the university
grading my students' papers...

373
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:39,100
when I heard there was an issue
at the Dream Resort.

374
00:21:40,170 --> 00:21:43,370
I was simply on my way to take a look.

375
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:46,310
I see.

376
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,810
But still, someone died.

377
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:50,810
You got out pretty quick, though.

378
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:53,580
I guess having my mom pull some strings
really helps.

379
00:21:53,950 --> 00:21:58,060
Seo Rin. They've already determined
that the victim was at fault.

380
00:21:58,320 --> 00:21:59,990
But that's not the point.

381
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,490
The victim died in the accident.

382
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:04,830
But the one responsible goes unpunished
and is just walking around freely?

383
00:22:04,830 --> 00:22:05,930
Does that make any sense?

384
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:09,170
The victim's family must feel
so wronged and angry.

385
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,670
Don't you think so?

386
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:14,300
Would you be saying this
if I were the one who died, Mom?

387
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,540
- You wouldn't, right?
- That's enough.

388
00:22:17,110 --> 00:22:18,840
There are some things you just don't say.

389
00:22:19,340 --> 00:22:21,110
And this is certainly not
the time or place.

390
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:23,250
Fine, I won't say another word.

391
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,680
Gosh, you're so scary.

392
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:28,050
Actually, Professor Kang
is the real victim.

393
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,750
The victim was drunk, lying on the road.

394
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,160
How could anyone have avoided hitting him?

395
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,120
We all drive, don't we?

396
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:36,460
This could happen to any of us
at any time.

397
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:42,170
I guess you must feel pretty wronged
since it happened while working for us.

398
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:45,200
Is that why Mom's taking
such special care of you?

399
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:47,940
Seo Rin. Are you going to keep
acting this disrespectfully?

400
00:22:48,540 --> 00:22:50,440
Okay, I get it.

401
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,080
Professor, I'm so sorry.

402
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:56,180
This invitation was so sudden,

403
00:22:56,610 --> 00:22:59,480
and I hope Seo Rin's rudeness
didn't upset you.

404
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,220
Not at all. It's fine.

405
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:02,950
It's only natural for her to be curious.

406
00:23:03,820 --> 00:23:07,060
Our professor is so understanding.
He is a true intellectual.

407
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:09,360
I wonder if that intellect is what
made my mom fall for you.

408
00:23:10,690 --> 00:23:14,930
If you weren't married,
you'd be a perfect match for my mom.

409
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,500
What is with you?

410
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,640
There's something
I've been wondering myself.

411
00:23:21,270 --> 00:23:22,640
Professor Kang,

412
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:25,810
were you really on such good terms
with my daughter-in-law...

413
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:28,380
for you to send her flowers?

414
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:42,960
Chairman Ma.

415
00:23:43,530 --> 00:23:47,530
I was hesitant to bring this up.

416
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:51,070
However, I feel
I should tell you the truth.

417
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:59,380
CEO Chae. I'm sorry.

418
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,950
I wasn't the one who sent the flowers.

419
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:05,620
What?

420
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:08,450
We already got our story straight.
You can't back out now.

421
00:24:08,990 --> 00:24:10,520
When Manager Park heard that...

422
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,420
CEO Chae was named
one of the top three female CEOs,

423
00:24:14,190 --> 00:24:16,360
he must have sent them in my name.

424
00:24:16,660 --> 00:24:19,860
Since I had done consulting
for Dream Hotel,

425
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:23,530
he said it was only right
for me to congratulate her.

426
00:24:23,930 --> 00:24:26,800
So that's what happened.

427
00:24:27,870 --> 00:24:29,170
Is that so?

428
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:32,180
I could have explained over the phone,

429
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:34,040
but I feared it'd sound like an excuse.

430
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:37,080
So I accepted your invitation, Chairman.

431
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,980
Now, don't go jumping...

432
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:43,890
to conclusions that I invited you...

433
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:46,390
because I'm suspicious of you two.

434
00:24:46,890 --> 00:24:49,530
You laid such a solid foundation
for our Dream Project,

435
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:51,960
and I was so grateful to you...

436
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:54,360
that I wanted to invite you over
for a meal and talk. That's all.

437
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,600
Chairman, please excuse me.

438
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:03,010
That's my wife calling.

439
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:04,570
Go ahead, take it.

440
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:05,880
Professor.

441
00:25:06,210 --> 00:25:09,310
Lawyer Han came to see me
a little while ago.

442
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,880
Did she happen to mention
anything about it afterwards?

443
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:16,620
When you're done,
could you let me speak to her?

444
00:25:17,690 --> 00:25:18,720
Sure.

445
00:25:24,530 --> 00:25:25,830
Hey, honey. Where are you?

446
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:27,600
We're about to have some chicken and beer.

447
00:25:29,430 --> 00:25:33,770
Chairman Ma invited me to dinner,
so I'm at his house.

448
00:25:35,110 --> 00:25:38,880
By the way, honey,
CEO Chae has something to say to you.

449
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,440
You're at Chairman Ma's house?

450
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:45,320
Anyway, put CEO Chae on.

451
00:25:45,620 --> 00:25:47,950
Dad is meeting with CEO Chae at this hour?

452
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:51,020
Okay, hold on.

453
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:57,490
Lawyer Han, this is Chae Hwa Young.

454
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:59,900
Yes. Hello.

455
00:26:00,530 --> 00:26:02,730
I hear you wanted to speak to me?

456
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:06,840
I was calling about my proposal
for our children to get married.

457
00:26:08,370 --> 00:26:10,640
I believe I already told you.

458
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:14,110
I said I'd respect Jun Ho's decision.

459
00:26:15,010 --> 00:26:18,450
In that case,
I'm holding you to your word.

460
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:19,780
Then.

461
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:24,850
Oh, Professor, I'm so sorry. Oh, a napkin!

462
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:28,220
- The bathroom's over there. I'm so sorry.
- Right.

463
00:26:28,430 --> 00:26:29,430
What have I done?

464
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,530
What was that all about?

465
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:38,840
You're arranging a marriage
with that family without my permission?

466
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:41,370
Father. My clothes got a little wet.

467
00:26:41,570 --> 00:26:44,110
I'll explain after I go and change.

468
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:54,320
That CEO Chae is really something else.

469
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,850
What does she mean
she's holding me to my word?

470
00:26:56,850 --> 00:26:57,920
What?

471
00:26:58,460 --> 00:26:59,760
What are you talking about, Mom?

472
00:27:00,090 --> 00:27:02,760
CEO Chae said she wanted you
as her son-in-law.

473
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:06,200
I told her I would follow your decision.

474
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:09,930
But then she asks me out of the blue
if I've reconsidered.

475
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,970
But didn't CEO Chae use to hate your guts?

476
00:27:12,540 --> 00:27:13,900
What's with this sudden son-in-law talk?

477
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,010
Seriously, what is it?

478
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:18,580
Did something happen
between you and her daughter?

479
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,010
Of course nothing happened.

480
00:27:20,940 --> 00:27:24,150
I have no idea why CEO Chae
has suddenly taken such a liking to me.

481
00:27:34,490 --> 00:27:35,530
CEO Chae.

482
00:27:36,090 --> 00:27:37,830
Why on earth would you say
something like that?

483
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:42,430
Why do you keep pushing
for Jun Ho and Director Ma to get married?

484
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:43,500
Quiet.

485
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:46,600
Professor, I had no choice.

486
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:49,240
Father suspects us.

487
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:52,010
Are you bringing up their marriage...

488
00:27:52,010 --> 00:27:54,640
just because you're afraid
we'll get caught?

489
00:27:55,780 --> 00:27:59,520
This is an absurd solution.
That marriage is out of the question.

490
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:01,950
It was because of us.

491
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:05,320
So even after the car accident,
to keep you out of it,

492
00:28:05,390 --> 00:28:07,560
I covered for you the best I could.

493
00:28:14,330 --> 00:28:16,100
When my dad got into that car accident,

494
00:28:16,870 --> 00:28:20,270
he covered for Chae Hwa Young
to protect her?

495
00:28:38,660 --> 00:28:40,390
(The First Man)

496
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,530
You get what I'm saying, right?

497
00:28:42,530 --> 00:28:44,090
Make sure you call this number.

498
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:46,460
Goodness, why did you drink so much?

499
00:28:46,630 --> 00:28:49,270
You've really changed, Director Ma.

500
00:28:49,530 --> 00:28:52,040
You're nothing like the Director Ma
I used to know.

501
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:53,840
Is that a compliment?

502
00:28:53,970 --> 00:28:55,310
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

503
00:28:55,670 --> 00:28:58,370
- Jang Mi, it's me.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

504
00:28:58,810 --> 00:29:00,010
But you're Jang Mi, aren't you?

505
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,010
What happened?

506
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:07,750
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
